        "text": "A1 Let A and B be points on the same branch of the hyper- bola xy = 1. Suppose that P is a point lying between A and B on this hyperbola, such that the area of the tri- angle APB is as large as possible. Show that the re- gion bounded by the hyperbola and the chord AP has the same area as the region bounded by the hyperbola and the chord PB.",
